===Continuous probability distribution===
Let formula_4 be a random variable following an absolutely continuous probability distribution with density function formula_51 (a function of formula_3) which depends on a parameter formula_1. Then the function

formula_54

considered as a function of formula_1, is the &quot;likelihood function&quot; (of formula_1, given the outcome formula_57). Again, formula_49 is not a probability density or mass function over formula_1, despite being a function of formula_1 given the observation formula_17.

====Relationship between the likelihood and probability density functions====
The use of the probability density in specifying the likelihood function above is justified as follows. Given an observation formula_62, the likelihood for the interval formula_63, where formula_64 is a constant, is given by formula_65. Observe that
